  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\(surjective)::function:from{A}:to{B}]\nRefines: f(x__)\nwhen: A, B is \\set\nsatisfies:\n. forAll: y \"in\" B\n  then:\n  . exists: x \"in\" A\n    suchThat: f(x) = y\nDocumented:\n. adjective: \"surjective\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{surjective}\"\n. description: \"A function $f \\colon A \\to B$ is surjective when for every $b \\in B$ there exists $a \\in A$ such that $f(a) = b$; every element of the codomain is attained.\"\nId: \"1de3c455-b09b-4d80-8b44-7dd223da2083\"",
